value.value: A technique used to measure the diameter of a single pupil in response to stimuli.
A type of angiographic procedure that allows for direct quantitative assessment of the native coronary arteries or bypass grafts supplying native coronary arteries.
A type of angiographic procedure that allows for direct quantitative assessment of the vessels of the hands, arms, feet and legs.
A method in which a probe is bounced off of the surface of the cornea, creating an induction current that is used to calculate intraocular pressure.
Any bacteria that does not require oxygen to grow or respirate and has a peptidoglycan rich cell wall that stains dark purple with the Gram staining technique
A genus of parasitic nematodes within the family Ancylostomatidae that are commonly found in dogs and cats. Infestation causes ancylostomiasis.
A species of pseudohyphae fungus belonging to the genus Candida that has been isolated from human skin, throat, and feces; it is a rare human pathogen in nosocomial infections.
The presence of more than one fungal and/or bacterial organism in a culture.

A genus of fungi within the phylum Zygomycota that are ubiquitous in nature and generally not considered pathogenic. Members of the Mucor genus produce apical, globular sporangia supported by columella, and do not produce rhizoids. Though generally thermointolerant, at least one species, Mucor indicus, may cause opportunistic infections in immunocompromised individuals to include zygomycosis.
A species of grey mycelium fungi belonging to the genus Rhizomucor that is most commonly found in compost heaps; it is a rare human pathogen, causing pulmonary, disseminated or cutaneous infection.

label.value: Mean Residence Time Infinity Observed by Extravascular Dose

value.value: The mean residence time (MRT) extrapolated to infinity for a substance administered by extravascular dosing, calculated using the observed value of the last non-zero concentration. Extravascular MRT includes Mean Absorption Time (MAT). (CDISC)

label.value: Mean Residence Time Infinity Predicted by Extravascular Dose

value.value: The mean residence time (MRT) extrapolated to infinity for a substance administered by extravascular dosing, calculated using the predicted value of the last non-zero concentration. Extravascular MRT includes Mean Absorption Time (MAT). (CDISC)

label.value: Mean Residence Time to Last Nonzero Concentration by Extravascular Dose

value.value: Mean residence time (MRT) from the time of dosing to the time of the last measurable concentration for a substance administered by extravascular dosing. Extravascular MRT includes Mean Absorption Time (MAT). (CDISC)
